		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />To quote a Bard's Tale fanpage:
<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://bardstale.brotherhood.de/talefiles/index.html">http://bardstale.brotherhood.de/talefiles/index.html</a><!-- m -->
<br />
<br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">The NES version of The Bard's Tale was drasticly different from all other versions of the game.</div>
<br />
<br />They even list it besides the regular series in the frameset.
<br />
<br />It has a different title screen, all different music, all different graphics, and numerous gameplay changes:
<br />
<br />No Races to choose from.
<br />No Paladin/Monk/Conjurer/Magician classes
<br />Different spells
<br />Different Bard Songs
<br />Completely redesigned and slightly smaller dungeons
<br />No icon bar for spell effects
<br />
<br />All these changes don't ruin the game though. It still undoubtedly is The Bard's Tale. On the plus side, the game gives you an automap feature right from the start.

		

